The paper discusses learning structured prediction models with latent variables, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of these models in computer vision applications, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses loss functions and optimization techniques, which could also place it in the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the search space and the effect of the latent space on generalization bounds, which could also place it in the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
